   <title type="text">Bible Gateway Blogger Grid (BG²)</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/blog/2013/12/bible-gateway-blogger-grid-bg%C2%B2/">Bible Gateway Blogger Grid (BG²)</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img alt="http://bg3-blog.s3.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/bg-blogger-badge-500x500-e1387301563797.jpg" class="decoded" height="200" src="http://bg3-blog.s3.amazonaws.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/bg-blogger-badge-500x500-e1387301563797.jpg" width="200" /> </blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;">Bible Gateway Blogger Grid (BG²) is an international&nbsp;network of  independent bloggers who meaningfully blog—and who are serious—about  matters relating to the Bible. Follow the members on Twitter using our <a href="https://twitter.com/biblegateway/lists/bg-blogger-grid-bg%C2%B2" target="_blank" title="Twitter List of Bible Gateway Blogger Grid Members">BG² List</a>.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">With the hashtag <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23bgbg2&amp;src=typd&amp;f=realtime" target="_blank" title="Bible Gateway Blogger Grid Hashtag #bgbg2">#bgbg2</a>,  BG² reflects a broad array of blogs: from mommy bloggers to writers to  pastors to seminaries to Bible professors and others, writing from North  &amp; South America, Europe, Asia, and Australia.</span><br /><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">Below is the title&nbsp;list of charter blogs that are on the Grid. <a href="mailto:jonathan.petersen@biblegateway.com?Subject=Blogger%20Grid%20Inquiry" target="_blank">Let us know</a> if you’re a blogger who’d like to receive an invitation to join BG².</span><br /></blockquote>]]></content>
